snippet.title: ZACH WINTERS /// Fernweh (Shore)
snippet.description:
"Fernweh (Shore)" from the album, Monarch
Buy: https://zachwinters.bandcamp.com/
Tour: https://www.zachwinters.com/shows/
Stream: https://fanlink.to/zachwinters
Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/user/ZachWintersMusica

Follow Zach Winters
Follow on Spotify: https://spoti.fi/2D3nsbF
Follow on Apple Music: https://apple.co/2yxKRhH
http://www.zachwinters.com
https://www.instagram.com/thezachwinters/
https://www.facebook.com/pg/Zach-Winters-Music-100663509995973

"There's something communal about Zach Winters' music, a hushed experience best seen, heard, and felt within an arm's reach. His music is a blend of acoustic folk that goes beyond Americana to something even more native. Zach's song, 'Fernweh (Shore)', begged to be shared while he played in our studio, like people gathering around a warm fire." — Musicbed

Amber Mattfield – Alaskan violin
Caleb Friesen — tasteful German cajon
Lane Winters – sweet sweet vocals
Zach Winters – the Australian guitar, choir conducting & vocals

filmed by Musicbed at Musicbed HQ in Fort Worth, TX.

License this song and more by Zach Winters: https://www.zachwinters.com/contact/
